The phase structures of bulk C3N4, CNT, CNT/Ni2P-0.5% and CNT/NCDs/Ni2P-0.5% were investigated by X-ray diffraction (XRD) (Fig. 1
                     ). The former angle diffraction peak at 13.2° was assigned to in-plane tri-s-triazine units (100) reflections, and the latter peak at 27.3° belonged to the interlayer stacking of graphitic structure [26]. Compared with bulk C3N4, the intensity of (100) peak in C3N4 nanotube decrease, which demonstrated that the periodic structure of the trithiazine skeleton is progressively lost [27]. The results of XRD of CNT/Ni2P-0.5% and CNT/NCDs/Ni2P-0.5% were similar to that of bulk C3N4. The intensity of diffraction peak at 27.3° for CNT/NCDs/Ni2P-0.5% is obviously weaker than CNT/Ni2P-0.5% after introducing NCDs, which is probably because that the presence of NCDs hinder the thermopolymerization of tri-s-triazine units and the stacking (crystallization) of g-C3N4 
                     [28]. Meanwhile, the enlarge XRD patterns (Fig. 1b) of CNT/Ni2P-0.5% and CNT/NCDs/Ni2P-0.5% showed no significant shift compared with CNT, indicating that the coupling of Ni2P and NCDs with CNT did not change the structure of C3N4, which was accordance with that reported in the literature [29]. In addition, no conspicuous peak of Ni2P was observed in the CNT/NCDs/Ni2P -0.5% composite due to the low quantity of Ni2P.

The FTIR spectra (Fig. 5
                     ) were obtained to investigate the molecular structure of the as-sample. In Fig. 5a, for pure C3N4 and CNT/NCDs/Ni2P-0.5%, the exist of a broad IR band between 1750 cm−1 and 800 cm−1 corresponded to heptazine heterocyclic ring units and the vibration characteristic of s-triazine ring units [38]. The band at around 3172 cm−1 could be attrbbuted to the N-H stretching vibration [39]. The formation of P-N or P-C groups had no observable signal, indicating that there was no phosphorus doping in the structure of C3N4 
                     [40]. Semblable FTIR band information was found in CNT/NCDs/Ni2P composites with different Ni2P loading ratio (Fig. 5b). The consenquences demonstrated that CNT/NCDs/Ni2P composites was unchanged structure with different Ni2P loading ratio, which was consistent with XRD measurement.
